The paper deals with the MacWilliams-type identity, which is a concept in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of posets and their properties, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of weight enumerators is also used, which is a common tool in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of hierarchical structures, which can be related to the field of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the classification of certain types of poset-block spaces, which can be considered a problem in computational complexity (cs.SI).
